      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented QA process and version control meets MRL 2 requirement of Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent v19.2 is a commercially validated solver with documented software QA procedures, release notes, and regression test suites. Version control and audit trail requirements at Gradation 1 are satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark verification cases relevant to rotating machinery internal flows at Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against standard CFD benchmark cases including lid-driven cavity and rotating disk flows. Published verification documentation from the vendor satisfies Gradation 1 for numerical code verification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for primary QoI (hemolysis index) with GCI < 5% on fine grid, demonstrating Gradation 2 discretization error control.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed using 2.1M, 4.8M, and 9.6M cell meshes. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI = 3.2% for the normalized index of hemolysis on the fine mesh, meeting the Gradation 2 threshold. The 4.8M cell mesh was selected for production runs as the best balance of accuracy and computational cost."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) match simulation boundary conditions within stated uncertainty bounds at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data were collected at five flow-speed combinations (2–8 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) using phosphate-buffered saline with bovine blood. Boundary conditions in the CFD model were set to match reported experimental values; fluid viscosity and density were matched within 2% of reported experimental values, satisfying Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) agrees with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values at all five operating points fell within ±20% of experimental measurements from the FDA benchmark dataset. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion was met for the candidate device relative to the predicate at all operating points, satisfying Gradation 2 output comparison requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The NIH and relative hemolysis index are directly linked to the clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis and are the accepted QoIs for CPB device assessment at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis is the standard metric for quantifying pump-induced blood damage per ASTM F1841. The relative hemolysis index RH directly compares candidate to predicate device performance. Both QoIs are clinically meaningful and directly support the regulatory decision, satisfying Gradation 2 relevance requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities use a geometrically similar pump under clinically representative flow conditions, providing Gradation 2 relevance to the CPB COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump, which shares key geometric features (impeller diameter, blade count, volute geometry) with the candidate CPB device. Operating conditions span the clinical range for CPB (2–8 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). The validation scenario is sufficiently representative of the COU to satisfy Gradation 2."
    },
    {
