      "rationale": "Simulation analysts hold graduate-level CFD training and followed documented standard operating procedures for pump hemolysis simulation. Independent review of model setup was performed. Use error controls at Gradation 1 are satisfied without formal use error assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; use of established turbulence and hemolysis models with literature support satisfies Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model are established formulations with extensive literature validation for rotary blood pump applications. Model form selection is documented and justified. Gradation 1 is satisfied without formal model form uncertainty quantification."
    },
    {
